    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Off the top of my head, I can think of two real reasons (i.e. have impacted me) to have sounds play in the menu:\r\n1. Tweaking volumes to balance e.g. sounds, music, Discord/TeamSpeak. The lack of sounds now makes this a frustrating iterative process. \r\n2. The aforementioned ability to see if your attention is needed (structure built, silos needed, base under attack, etc), especially in a multiplayer game where pausing is not realistic. \r\n\r\nWhat are the motivations to mute sounds in menu? "
  },
