    "created_at": "2017-06-08T13:57:25Z",
    "updated_at": "2017-06-08T13:57:25Z",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Indeed, in single-player mode (skirmish, mission, 'multiplayer' vs AI), the game pauses when you open the menu, so sounds stop. \r\n\r\nIn multiplayer, where it doesn't pause when the menu is opened, I think that all sounds should continue playing. I think I noticed when this stopped being the case and found it disruptive. Players have the option to mute (m) before going into multiplayer menu.\r\n\r\nA possible issue with your solution to issue 1, @WolfGaming, is that a slider-bar sound would be a poor proxy for the actual in-game sounds. Then, there is still issue 2."
  },
